ermediaries-to-play-key-role-in-future-of-data-for-development-86158\" target=\"_blank\">\'Intermediaries\' to play key role in future of data for development</a>\" by Kelli Rogers, devex.com, May 19, 2015.&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		\"<a href=\"http://post2015.org/2015/05/06/life-after-the-cartagena-data-festival-well-never-be-the-same/\" target=\"_blank\">Life After the Cartagena Data Festival – We’ll Never Be the Same</a>\" by Kristen Stelljes, Program Officer, Hewlett Foundation, May 6, 2015.		&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n	</div>&#13;\r\n	&#13;\r\n</div></body>','Celebrating the Outcomes of the Cartagena Data Festival','','publish','open','open','','post-2015-06-09-blog-cartoon-movement-competition-cartagena-data-festival','','','2015-09-06 02:40:30','2015-09-06 02:40:30','',0,'http://datapop.wpengine.com/?p=110',0,'post','',0),(111,3,'2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','','reality_through_the_ipod_screen__miguel_villalba_snchez__elchicotriste_','','inherit','open','closed','','reality_through_the_ipod_screen__miguel_villalba_snchez__elchicotriste_','','','2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','',110,'http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/reality_through_the_ipod_screen__miguel_villalba_snchez__elchicotriste_.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(112,3,'2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','','1TYIH4xgHgvQwNKvby4vktulTsU3Q2tHaj7kC75Q60Y=w830-h553-no','','inherit','open','closed','','1tyih4xghgvqwnkvby4vktultsu3q2thaj7kc75q60yw830-h553-no','','','2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','',110,'http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1TYIH4xgHgvQwNKvby4vktulTsU3Q2tHaj7kC75Q60Yw830-h553-no',0,'attachment','',0),(113,3,'2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','','the_evolution__fadi_abou_hassan','','inherit','open','closed','','the_evolution__fadi_abou_hassan','','','2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','',110,'http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/the_evolution__fadi_abou_hassan.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(114,3,'2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','','1eq_hkJ6uTXHHUvFsxRJnW0v-y7QGYtUx5rTiAlhNoo=w486-h553-no','','inherit','open','closed','','1eq_hkj6utxhhuvfsxrjnw0v-y7qgytux5rtialhnoow486-h553-no','','','2015-09-06 01:15:00','2015-09-06 01:15:00','',110,'http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1eq_hkJ6uTXHHUvFsxRJnW0v-y7QGYtUx5rTiAlhNoow486-h553-no',0,'attachment','',0),(116,2,'2015-06-09 01:15:11','2015-06-09 01:15:11','[embed]https://www.youtube.com/embed/OS1SfGzb04Q[/embed]<body><div class=\"custom-post\" id=\"cdf-outcomes\">&#13;\r\n		<p>With over 400 registered participants, 3 days filled with events and presentations and countless stimulating conversations, the Cartagena Data Festival was an extraordinary experience and in our opinion, a great success. The festival was livestreamed for people following from home, and interacted with the Twitter community\'s questions and comments. Simultaneous translation was available for non-English speaking attendees. </p>&#13;\r\n			&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:24%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/16668477284\" title=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/16668477284_06153beb23_b.jpg\" alt=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:50%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/17103385560\" title=\"dia 1 (baja)-98 by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/17103385560_ba7e42b460_b.jpg\" alt=\"dia 1 (baja)-98\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p>Questions were taken from a social media feed during plenary sessions</p>&#13;\r\n		</div>		&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:24%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/16668482004\" title=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/16668482004_7a16e7882f_b.jpg\" alt=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/17290937595\" title=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/17290937595_1e93c6e023_b.jpg\" alt=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p>There was live translation in all sessions</p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n&#13;\r\n		<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" lang=\"en\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Full house at <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/BigData?src=hash\">#BigData</a> track in Cartagena <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/data2015?src=hash\">#data2015</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/Jww6V18DGv\">pic.twitter.com/Jww6V18DGv</a></p>— Data-Pop Alliance (@datapopalliance) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/datapopalliance/status/590238876943265792\">April 20, 2015</a></blockquote>&#13;\r\n		<script async=\"\" src=\"//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"/><div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:24%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/18162107141\" title=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/18162107141_6db0d979f8_b.jpg\" alt=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:50%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/18162109871\" title=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/18162109871_41b31dd59f_b.jpg\" alt=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p><a href=\"/people#bio-letouze\">Emmanuel Letouzé</a> speaks in one of the plenary sessions</p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:24%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/17103162748\" title=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/17103162748_516796a247_b.jpg\" alt=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<h3>ODI has assmebled a playlist of interviews with key participants:</h3>&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"videoBoxWrapper\">&#13;\r\n			<div class=\"videoBox 16-9\" style=\"text-align:center;\">&#13;\r\n				<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PL8sELjFjXUp9ZV0_jR-2eAHNL9XSG3ERs\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"/>&#13;\r\n			</div>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<h3><a href=\"http://twitter.com/jorgemartin\">Jorge Martin</a> was responsible for amazing graphic scribing done in real time at the event:</h3>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:100%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/17115118728\" title=\"Mural of the conference by @jorgemartin (© Jorge Martin) by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/17115118728_161b38ec14_k.jpg\" alt=\"Mural of the conference by @jorgemartin (© Jorge Martin)\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/17290636561\" title=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/17290636561_977a55cec4_b.jpg\" alt=\"© Oficina de Prensa Departamento Estadístico Nacional de Estadística - DANE\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n&#13;\r\n		<h3>The Human Development Report Office organized a <a href=\"http://www.cartagenadatafest2015.org/#nav-competition\">Data Visualization Competition</a> especially for the event, which received 80 submissions from 29 countries.</h3>&#13;\r\n		<p>The winning visualization is <a href=\"http://hdrdata.tumblr.com/post/116301023888/top-9-human-development-tree\">The Human Development Tree</a> by Jurjen Verhagen, an engineer and interactive visualization specialist from the Netherlands. Verhagen and the other two finalist entries, <a href=\"http://hdrdata.tumblr.com/post/116301020078/top-9-close-the-gap\">Close the Gap</a> by Ri Liu and <a href=\"http://hdrdata.tumblr.com/post/116301030248/top-9-visualizing-the-2013-human-development\">Visualizing the 2013 Human Development Index</a> by InKyung Choi and her team, were invited to the festival to receive their awards from the Mayor of Cartagena and the Deputy Director of HDRO, in front of hundreds of data artists and scientists from around the world.</p>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:49%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/17974657569\" title=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/17974657569_164521c144_b.jpg\" alt=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		<div class=\"cdf-photo\" style=\"width:49%;\">&#13;\r\n			<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/18134396026\" title=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz by Cartagena Data Festival, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/18134396026_f77ccf1339_b.jpg\" alt=\"©CEPEI/Helkin René Díaz\"/></a>&#13;\r\n			<p> </p>&#13;\r\n		</div>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<h3>Many participants and partners published reflections about the festival.</h3>&#13;\r\n		<p>You can pieces by Kristen Stelljes, Program Officer at the Hewlett Foundation, <a href=\"http://post2015.org/2015/05/06/life-after-the-cartagena-data-festival-well-never-be-the-same/\">here</a>; as well as Clare Melamed\'s\' <a href=\"http://www.developmentprogress.org/blog/2015/05/01/welcome-data-revolution\">article</a> for Development Progress and Kelli Rogers\' <a href=\"https://www.devex.com/news/traditional-vs-citizen-generated-data-is-it-a-case-of-either-or-85975\">summary</a>. Devex also has interviews from the festival <a href=\"https://www.devex.com/news/intermediaries-to-play-key-role-in-future-of-data-for-development-86158\">here</a>, including with Data-Pop\'s Director, Emmanuel Letouzé.</p>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<p>&#13;\r\n		\"<a href=\"https://www.devex.com/news/traditional-vs-citizen-generated-data-is-it-a-case-of-either-or-85975\" target=\"_blank\">Traditional vs. citizen-generated data: Is it a case of either-or?</a>\" by Kelli Rogers, devex.com, April 23, 2015.&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		\"<a href=\"https://www.devex.com/news/intermediaries-to-play-key-role-in-future-of-data-for-development-86158\" target=\"_blank\">\'Intermediaries\' to play key role in future of data for development</a>\" by Kelli Rogers, devex.com, May 19, 2015.&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		\"<a href=\"http://post2015.org/2015/05/06/life-after-the-cartagena-data-festival-well-never-be-the-same/\" target=\"_blank\">Life After the Cartagena Data Festival – We’ll Never Be the Same</a>\" by Kristen Stelljes, Program Officer, Hewlett Foundation, May 6, 2015.	&#13;\r\n		</p>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<h3>Congratulations to the winners of the Cartoon Movement competition!</h3>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<p>We are pleased to announce the 4 winning cartoons, selected by voters at the Cartagena Data Festival and on the Cartoon Movement website. Thank you to all who participated and voted!</p>&#13;\r\n		<p>Please click on these winning cartoons to Tweet about them:</p>&#13;\r\n		&#13;\r\n		<style type=\"text/css\"><![CDATA[		\r\n			#DataCartoonWinners td { width:50%; text-align:center; }		\r\n			#DataCartoonWinners img { margin:20px 10%; width:80%; }		\r\n			#DataCartoonWinners .title { font-weight:bold; margin:0; }		\r\n			#DataCartoonWinners .caption { font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; margin:0; }		\r\n			#DataCartoonWinners .author { font-style:italic; margin:0; }\r\n		]]></style><table id=\"DataCartoonWinners\"><tr><td>&#13;\r\n					<figure><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?hashtags=DataCartoon15%2C&amp;original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fcartoons&amp;share_with_retweet=never&amp;tw_p=tweetbutton&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fcartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fdatacartoon15\">&#13;\r\n							<img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/reality_through_the_ipod_screen__miguel_villalba_snchez__elchicotriste_1.jpg\"/></a>&#13;\r\n						<figcaption><p class=\"title\">#DataCartoon15:<br/>Reality through the iPod screen</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"caption\">We are more and more used to ignoring empirical reality to enclose ourselves in the digital version.</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"author\">By <a href=\"http://www.cartoonmovement.com/p/2729\" target=\"blank\">Miguel Villalba Sánchez (Elchicotriste)</a> (Spain)</p>&#13;\r\n						</figcaption></figure></td>&#13;\r\n				<td>&#13;\r\n					<figure><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?hashtags=DataCartoon19%2C&amp;original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fcartoons&amp;share_with_retweet=never&amp;tw_p=tweetbutton&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fcartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fdatacartoon19\">&#13;\r\n							<img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1TYIH4xgHgvQwNKvby4vktulTsU3Q2tHaj7kC75Q60Yw830-h553-no1\"/></a>&#13;\r\n						<figcaption><p class=\"title\">#DataCartoon19:<br/>Twitter</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"caption\">Tweets... freedom of expression</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"author\">By <a href=\"http://www.cartoonmovement.com/p/2456\" target=\"blank\">E L E N A . ospina</a> (Colombia)</p>&#13;\r\n						</figcaption></figure></td>&#13;\r\n			</tr><tr><td>&#13;\r\n					<figure><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?hashtags=DataCartoon17%2C&amp;original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fcartoons&amp;share_with_retweet=never&amp;tw_p=tweetbutton&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fcartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fdatacartoon17\">&#13;\r\n							<img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/the_evolution__fadi_abou_hassan1.jpg\"/></a>&#13;\r\n						<figcaption><p class=\"title\">#DataCartoon17:<br/>The Evolution</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"caption\">Data and Development</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"author\">By <a href=\"http://www.cartoonmovement.com/p/2628\" target=\"blank\">Fadi Abou Hassan</a> (Norway)</p>&#13;\r\n						</figcaption></figure></td>&#13;\r\n				<td>&#13;\r\n					<figure><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?hashtags=DataCartoon3%2C&amp;original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fcartoons&amp;share_with_retweet=never&amp;tw_p=tweetbutton&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fcartagenadatafest2015.org%2Fdatacartoon3\">&#13;\r\n							<img src=\"http://datapop.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1eq_hkJ6uTXHHUvFsxRJnW0v-y7QGYtUx5rTiAlhNoow486-h553-no1\"/></a>&#13;\r\n						<figcaption><p class=\"title\">#DataCartoon3:<br/>Data and local cultures</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"caption\">A cartoon about the local cultures, the poverty and new technologies</p>&#13;\r\n							<p class=\"author\">By <a href=\"http://www.cartoonmovement.com/p/6780\" target=\"blank\">Ares</a> (Cuba)</p>&#13;\r\n						</figcaption></figure></td>&#13;\r\n			</tr></table><p>The Cartoon Movement is a global collaborative platform for editorial cartoons and comics journalism that publishes new content at least four times a week. In the lead-up to the Cartagena Data Festival, <a href=\"http://www.cartoonmovement.com/newsroom?fq=subroom.54\" target=\"_blank\">the Cartoon Movement set up a newsroom</a> calling for submissions of artwork relating to data and development. A <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"/cartoons\">showcase of 19 cartoons</a> from this competition were <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/132666799@N08/18157248212/in/set-72157651806318610\">displayed throughout the festival</a> and  participants were asked to vote by <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23DataCartoon1%20OR%20%23DataCartoon2%20OR%20%23DataCartoon3%20OR%20%23DataCartoon4%20OR%20%23DataCartoon5%20OR%20%23DataCartoon6%20OR%20%23DataCartoon7%20OR%20%23DataCartoon8%20OR%20%23DataCartoon9%20OR%20%23DataCartoon10%20OR%20%23DataCartoon11%20OR%20%23DataCartoon12%20OR%20%23DataCartoon13%20OR%20%23DataCartoon14%20OR%20%23DataCartoon15%20OR%20%23DataCartoon16%20OR%20%23DataCartoon17%20OR%20%23DataCartoon18%20OR%20%23DataCartoon19\">Tweeting their favourite cartoon</a>. The showcased cartoons were selected for their relevance to the festival\'s goals—to stir discussions and connections in the data (open data, big data, official statistics) and development community, to lay out the opportunities and challenges, risks and requirements, of leveraging the new data ecosystem to foster human development—and votes were collected in the Cartoon Movement newsroom and through Tweets sent by festival participants. Please feel free to Tweet about the winning entries (above) </p>&#13;\r\n	&#13;\r\n	</div>&#13;\r\n	&#13;\r\n</div></body>','Celebrating the Outcomes of the Cartagena Data Festival','','publish','open','open','','post-2015-06-09-blog-cartoon-movement-competition-cartagena-data-festival-v2','','','2015-09-06 02:05:54','2015-09-06 02:05:54','',0,'http://datapop.wpengine.com/?p=116',0,'post','',0),(117,3,'2015-09-06 01:15:11','201